<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="311" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,979,1005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet of the new species is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1062,1123,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">albus</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1176,1296,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="311">marginalis</emphasis>
, referring to the fringe of the forewing which is white from apex to middle of the termen distally.
</paragraph>
